author: AP
title: VIRUS DIARY: Fantasy baseball, when real ball is the fantasy
description: Baseball fans are trying in various ways to get their fixes while the “national pastime” is on hold because of the coronavirus outbreak
content: CINCINNATI (AP) — “People ask me what I do in winter when there is no baseball. I’ll tell you what I do. I stare out the window and wait for spring.” — Rogers Hornsby (1896-1963), baseball Hall of Famer
